  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And I weighed unto them the silver, and the gold, and the vessels,.... When he delivered them to them; this he did as a proof of his own integrity and faithfulness, and as a security against any charge or accusation of embezzling any part of them, and to set them an example, and also that they might be under no temptation of acting such a part, and might be vindicated should they be charged with it: even ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the offering of the house of our God; what was freely offered for the service of it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which the king and his counsellors, and his lords, and all Israel there present, had offered; as freewill offerings, see Ezra 7:15. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "which the king and his counsellors, and his lords, and all Israel there present, had offered; as freewill offerings, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 7:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
