      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " etc. We may gather from this that the silver and gold were in bars or ingots, and not in coined money. The Persians had coined money at this tin. e, but the Treasury kept the bulk of its stores in bars (Herod., 3:96). Ezra 8:25",
